Simulation_init.F90
Simulation_initBlock.F90
Simulation_initSpecies.F90
Simulation_data.F90

    Standard problem setup

Grid_markRefineDerefine.F90

    Modify paramesh code to refine on (1) nested z layers, (2) active
    (non-sink) particles that generate stellar winds and radiation.
    Combines three files:
        flash4.5-rad/source/Grid/GridMain/paramesh/Grid_markRefineDerefine.F90
        flash4.5-rad/source/Particles/ParticlesMain/active/Sink/Couple_AMUSE/Grid_markRefineDerefine.F90
        flash4.2.2-rad/source/Simulation/SimulationMain/StratBox_TracerParticles/Grid_markRefineDerefine.F90
    2019 March 28, AT

Grid_markRefineSpecialized.F90
gr_markInZ.F90
constants.h

    Modify paramesh code to refine on nested z layers.
    Refinement edits taken from:
        flash4.2.2-rad/source/Grid/GridMain/paramesh/Grid_markRefineSpecialized.F90
        flash4.2.2-rad/source/Grid/GridMain/paramesh/gr_markInZ.F90
        flash4.2.2-rad/source/Simulation/constants.h
    and manually verified up-to-date with FLASH4.5.
    2019 March 28, AT
    

gr_sanitizeDataAfterInterp.F90

    When cells go bad, report refinement level of the offending block.
    Taken from:
        flash4.2.2-rad/source/Grid/GridMain/paramesh/paramesh4/gr_sanitizeDataAfterInterp.F90
    and manually verified up-to-date with FLASH4.5.
    2019 March 28, AT

Gravity_accelOneRow.F90.mg
Particles_sinkAccelGasOnSinksAndSinksOnGas.F90
Simulation_addStaticAcceleration.F90
Simulation_interface.F90

    STATIC GRAVITY IMPLEMENTATION.

    Taken from:
        flash4.5-rad/source/physics/Gravity/GravityMain/Poisson/Gravity_accelOneRow.F90
        flash4.5-rad/source/Particles/ParticlesMain/active/Sink/Particles_sinkAccelGasOnSinksAndSinksOnGas.F90
        flash4.5-rad/source/Simulation/Simulation_interface.F90
        flash4.2.2-rad/source/Simulation/SimulationMain/StratBox_TracerParticles/grv_addStaticAcceleration.F90

    Verified that first two are same between FLASH4.5 and flash4.5-rad.

    WARNING: CURRENTLY ONLY COMPATIBLE WITH MULTIGRID.
    FOR BHTREE, NEED A DIFFERENT VERSION OF GRAVITY_ACCELONEROW.F90
